page.title: 17MILITARY AIRCRAFT
page.content: Military Aircraft fly over Chapel St. Leonards from R.A.F.'s Conigsby Scampton and Waddington which are bases inland. Tornado's,A10's,Phantom's,HS125's and Awac's have been spotted. The Tornado's,Phantom's and A10's are the most common. They normallay fly in three's or four's. They fly low and go out into the North sea .They practice bombing and low movements across land and sea. The engine noise often makes you jump but poeple are used to it now. Poeple with young babies don't like them because it scares young children. {B.GOLOB.} Aged 10
